-- Japan Talks With Saudis on Replacing Iranian Oil, Watan Reports
-- B y   W a e l   M a h d i
-- 2012-01-08T08:24:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-08/japan-talks-with-saudis-on-replacing-iranian-oil-watan-reports.html
Japan  asked  Saudi Arabia  to provide
more crude oil to compensate for any loss in shipments from
 Iran , al-Watan reported, citing a foreign ministry spokesman.  Foreign Minister  Koichiro Gemba  discussed security of oil
supply and stability of  oil prices  during a visit to  Riyadh 
yesterday, the Saudi  daily  reported, citing Masaru Sato from the
Japanese ministry.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wael Mahdi in Khobar, Saudi Arabia at 
 wmahdi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
